person_analysis.overview: Jen Dewalt is a Miami-based serial entrepreneur, software engineer, and designer. Best known for teaching herself to code by creating 180 websites in 180 days, she has since founded Zube, a GitHub-integrated project management platform. Her career spans technical leadership, growth strategy, UX design, and product development. With an MFA in Visual Art and a BA in Studio Art, Jen brings a creative, multidisciplinary approach to tech innovation.
person_analysis.executive_summary: Jen Dewalt is a self-taught developer turned serial entrepreneur, now founder of Zube. Her journey from MFA-trained artist to software engineer and startup founder has been marked by adaptability, creativity, and product leadership. She combines technical expertise in JavaScript and SaaS with experience in growth, branding, and UX design. Widely recognized for her 180 Websites in 180 Days project, Jen exemplifies the intersection of creativity and engineering in building user-focused technology products.
key_insights: Transitioned from an art background into software engineering and entrepreneurship.
Founder of multiple startups, with Zube as her longest-running venture.
Blends technical expertise with product, branding, and growth leadership.
Recognized speaker and visible advocate for self-directed learning in coding.
